Signal de veille — Infosecurity Mag.

The Five Eyes Alliance has published a rare call to action for organizations facing AI threats

The leaders of the Five Eyes cybersecurity agencies have warned that frontier AI will &ldquo;fundamentally&rdquo; transform offensive and defensive capabilities within months.

In a public statement issued on June 22, the UK, US, Canada, New Zealand and Australia called on business leaders to prioritize cyber resilience or risk facing &ldquo;growing operational and strategic disadvantage.&rdquo;

&ldquo;AI is not a future consideration &ndash; it is already here,&rdquo; the statement read.

&ldquo;It lowers barriers for malicious actors and increases the speed and complexity of attacks, shrinking the window between vulnerability discovery and exploitation ever more quickly. At the same time, AI offers powerful tools to strengthen defense.&rdquo;

Read more on frontier AI: Bank of England, FCA and Treasury Raise Alarm Over Frontier AI

The group urged a &ldquo;whole-of-organization&rdquo; and &ldquo;whole-of-society&rdquo; response based around &ldquo;getting the basics right, acting quickly, and integrating cyber security into core business strategy.&rdquo;
